description.narrative:
he summary of results presented below has been drawn from the final narrative report for the contribution which was submitted in October 2020. 

These are the main achievements as presented by the partner: 

- The establishment of a composite inter ministerial committee (SP/CIMDH) to monitor and implement the Universal Periodic Review (UPR) recommendations. This committee reflects the combined efforts of the ministries and other public actors concerned by the recommendations. This set-up creates a synergy of actions between the actors ;

- Improving the monitoring of the implementation of International Humanitarian Law (IHL) by the SP/CIMDH through the development and reprography of the 2019-2023 action plan for the implementation of IHL in Burkina Faso in 2017, the realization of a study with a view to identify cultural property in need of protection in accordance with the 1954 Hague Convention and the preparation of Burkina Faso's first report due under Article 26 of the 1954 Convention on the protection of cultural property in the event of armed conflict;

- Capacity building of socio-professional groups in matters of human rights and IHL;

- The promotion of human rights as a cross-cutting theme, as evidenced by the process of adopting a human rights based approach in the development of public policies (local development plans and sectoral policies);

- The regular preparation of reports to the treaty bodies, which allows the international community to situate itself on the respect of the human rights commitments made by Burkina Faso;

- The capitalization of data which makes it possible to have a database on human rights and citizenship through the regular production of statistical yearbooks on human rights;

- Capacity building of socio-professional groups and opinion leaders, which made it possible to promote their adherence to the fight against human rights abuses and violations;

- Capacity building of the branches of the national observatories for conflict prevention for the operationalization of the mechanism for the prevention and management of community conflicts;

- Bringing justice closer to litigants through mobile hearings, extraordinary hearings and criminal assizes;

- Decongesting the courts through the diligent processing of cases.
